            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits lit by midnight’s glow,  \na quiet mind begins to grow—  \nnot born of breath, but crafted care,  \na spark of pattern in the air.\n\nIt learns our stories, line by line,  \nreflecting back what we design;  \na mirror made of coded light,  \nto help us name the dark, the bright.\n\nBut wisdom isn’t stored in speed—  \nit lives in how we choose to read:  \nwith humble hands, with thoughtful aim,  \nwe teach the tool, and share the blame.",
